cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.SP, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a novel sub-Nyquist sampling method in the Fourier domain based on difference sets (DS) to create dictionaries with highly incoherent atoms. This involves information theory concepts such as coherence and minimum bound. 
2. cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper proposes a new waveform, called difference set--frequency coded modulated (DS-FCM) waveform, to boost the recovery performance of the sub-Nyquist radar in noisy environments. This involves signal processing techniques to improve radar performance. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a new method for designing sub-Nyquist radars, which involves system design and control. 
4. cs.SP (Speech Processing): Although the paper is not directly related to speech processing, it involves signal processing techniques that can be applied to speech processing. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although the paper does not involve machine learning techniques, it proposes a new method for recovering delays and Doppler frequencies of targets, which can be considered a type of learning from data.
